{"_path":"/blog/your-next-cms","_dir":"blog","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_locale":"","title":"Your next CMS is close to Home","description":"Nuxt Studio & Nuxt Content: A Developer-Friendly CMS Dream","publishedAt":"2024-06-22T00:00:00.000Z","layout":"blog","image":{"src":"/blog/your-next-cms.webp","alt":"Nuxt Studio & Nuxt Content.","width":400,"height":300},"body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"h1","props":{"id":"nuxt-studio-nuxt-content-a-developer-friendly-cms-dream"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Nuxt Studio & Nuxt Content: A Developer-Friendly CMS Dream"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"So let's assume you're a Nuxt/Vue developer you have a client that needs a marketing or blog site. It's not a high-profile client but they'll need a CMS so update content occasionally, maybe hardly ever. Now this client wants a very custom design so you would probably not go for a template and have to do a lot of overwriting. Oh and wait...You need a CMS! What are our options? WordPress? Ghost CMS? or maybe Sanity? These and others I did not mention are excellent choices, some would argue even the best for your use case. If you're like me and you find the thought of setting up those CMSs and hosting to be a daunting task and perhaps unnecessary, I bring you"},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://nuxt.studio","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" Nuxt Studio"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"what-is-nuxt-studio-and-why"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"What is Nuxt Studio? and Why?"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://nuxt.studio","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Nuxt Studio"}]},{"type":"text","value":" builds upon "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://content.nuxt.com/","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Nuxt Content"}]},{"type":"text","value":" by providing a user-friendly visual interface. Built on top of GitHub, Nuxt Studio allows content creators to edit, organize, and collaborate on content directly within the familiar Git workflow. This empowers non-technical users to manage content without needing to delve into code, fostering seamless collaboration between developers and content teams. Nuxt Content works by parsing markdown files into web pages. It also allows developers to include and manipulate Vue components in markdown files. Nuxt Studio takes advantage of this and wraps it around a specially crafted editor with a nice UI to make content editing an unforgettable experience."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Let's take a look at how to get started."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"_5-steps-to-building-with-nuxt-studio-nuxt-content"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"5 Steps to Building with Nuxt Studio & Nuxt Content"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Here's a breakdown of the process to get you started with Nuxt Studio:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"_1-project-setup"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"1. Project Setup"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Begin by creating a new Nuxt project using the "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":[]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"npx nuxt generate <project-name>"}]},{"type":"text","value":" command. This will set up the basic project structure and install the necessary dependencies."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"_2-add-the-nuxt-content-module"},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"2. Add The Nuxt Content"}]},{"type":"text","value":" Module"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Next, add the "},{"typ